OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FEx-lollipop lady died on   
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Froad she tried to make     
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Fsafer                      
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, A former lollipop lady died after she  
OL,6, was hit by a van on a road which she   
OL,7, had campaigned to make safer.          
OL,9,FIrene Allen, 87, was seriously injured 
OL,10,Fon Walmersley Road in Bury on 6        
OL,11,FDecember and died five days later,     
OL,12,FGreater Manchester Police (GMP) said.  
OL,14,FHer daughter Melanie paid tribute to   
OL,15,Fthe "first lollipop lady in Bury" whose
OL,16,F"sunny personality" would be missed.   
OL,18,FShe noted the "tragic irony" that her  
OL,19,Fmother had argued for safer crossings  
OL,20,Ffor children on the road in the 1960s. 
